      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Increased border security and stricter immigration enforcement are crucial for maintaining national security, preserving jobs for American citizens, and upholding the rule of law. Stronger border control prevents illegal immigration, which can lead to an influx of undocumented workers willing to accept lower wages, potentially driving down overall wage standards. Furthermore, ensuring that immigration laws are strictly enforced helps to deter criminal activities and human trafficking, as it sends a clear message that illegal activities will not be tolerated. Lastly, prioritizing border security allows for a more orderly and regulated immigration system, ensuring that those who do come to the country can do so legally and with proper documentation, which in turn supports public safety and social stability.",
