      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a good way to frame the balance. but if we're being really honest, many people argue that the \"rule of law\" argument is basically used as a shield to ignore the actual suffering caused by these policies. how would a debater respond if the opponent claims that focusing on \"orderly systems\" is just a way to prioritize bureaucratic efficiency over human life? is there actually a way to argue that legal frameworks are objectively more important than individual human rights in this context without sounding dismissive?",
